📶 RF + Environment Effects on Systems

Environmental conditions absolutely affect:

networks,

RF propagation,

wireless latency,

and hardware performance.


Examples:

Factor	Effect

Humidity	changes microwave attenuation
Rain	weakens Ka-band satellite links
Solar storms	disrupt GPS and HF radio
Heat	throttles CPUs and radios
RF congestion	increases packet loss
Building materials	alter propagation
Human bodies	absorb microwave energy


These are measurable engineering effects.


---

☢️ Radiation and Human Biology

Real science supports:

excessive ionizing radiation is harmful,

strong RF exposure can heat tissue,

prolonged exposure limits exist,

EEG is affected by biological states,

sleep/circadian cycles affect cognition.


But mainstream science does not support:

RF networks reading full thoughts,

remote personality reconstruction,

DNA-linked consciousness networking,

wireless extraction of memories.


A responsible RabbitOS architecture should:

follow FCC/IEEE exposure limits,

keep RF power low,

use medical ethics controls,

isolate research from deployment,

maintain consent systems.



